Contract Commencement                    July 1, 2026
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.3 SUBMISSION PROTOCOLS
Proposals must be submitted via the NSU eBid Portal (Bonfire).
- Volume I:   Technical Proposal (PDF, searchable). NO PRICING DATA.
- Volume II:  Cost Proposal (Excel Template provided).
- Volume III: Financial Viability & Legal Disclosures.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.0 GENERAL TERMS & CONDITIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2.1 TERM OF CONTRACT
The initial contract term shall be three (3) years beginning July 1, 2026, and 
ending June 30, 2029. The University reserves the right to renew for two (2) 
additional one-year periods (Total potential term: 5 years). Renewals are 
contingent upon a scorecard rating of >85% on quarterly business reviews (QBRs).

2.2 INSURANCE REQUIREMENTS
The successful Proposer shall carry the following minimum insurance coverage:
- Commercial General Liability: $2,000,000 per occurrence / $5,000,000 agg.
- Workers’ Compensation: Statutory Limits as required by the State.
- Automobile Liability: $1,000,000 combined single limit.
- Excess/Umbrella Liability: $10,000,000.
- Crime/Fidelity Bond: $500,000 (covering employee theft).

2.3 COMPLIANCE & BACKGROUND CHECKS
- Criminal History: Vendor must perform nationwide criminal background checks 
  (7-year lookback) and 10-panel drug screens on all employees prior to 
  placement. No personnel with felony convictions related to theft, violence, 
  or sexual offenses may work on campus.
- Badging: All vendor staff must display a University Contractor ID badge 
  above the waist at all times. Lost badges will incur a $50 replacement fee.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.0 SCOPE OF WORK (SOW) - TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3.1 FACILITY CLASSIFICATION & STANDARDS
The University utilizes APPA (Association of Physical Plant Administrators) 
Leadership in Educational Facilities standards.

- Group A (Executive/Admissions): APPA Level 1 (Orderly Spotlessness).
- Group B (Classrooms/Libraries/Labs): APPA Level 2 (Ordinary Tidiness).
- Group C (Admin Offices): APPA Level 3 (Casual Inattention).
- Group D (Athletic Concourses/Fieldhouse): Event-Driven.

3.2 DETAILED SPECIFICATIONS BY AREA

3.2.1 Hard Surface Floors (VCT, Terrazzo, Polished Concrete)
- Daily: Dust mop with treated microfiber. Spot damp mop spills.
- Weekly: Auto-scrub high-traffic corridors and lobbies.
- Quarterly: Machine scrub and recoat (top scrub) VCT areas.
- Annually: Complete strip and refinish (4 coats min) of all VCT.
  (Must be scheduled during Winter Break or Summer Session).

3.2.2 Carpeted Floors
- Daily: Spot clean stains. Vacuum traffic lanes in lobbies/classrooms.
- Weekly: Wall-to-wall vacuuming of offices and conference rooms.
- Semi-Annually: Hot water extraction (steam clean) of all carpeted areas.
  (Bonnet cleaning is NOT permitted as a substitute for extraction).

3.2.3 Restrooms & Locker Rooms (Critical Focus Area)
- Frequency: All academic restrooms must be fully cleaned/disinfected nightly.
- Day Porter Service: High-volume restrooms (Student Union, Library) require 
  three (3) daily police checks (10a, 2p, 6p) to restock paper and remove trash.
- Deep Clean: Monthly machine scrub of ceramic tile floors and grout restoration.

3.2.4 Laboratories (BSL-1 & BSL-2)
- Vendor staff may ONLY perform floor care and empty trash from designated 
  "General Waste" bins.
- RESTRICTIONS: Vendor staff shall not touch lab benches, sinks, or equipment. 
  Red "Biohazard" bags are NOT to be touched by custodial staff.

3.3 GREEN CLEANING & SUSTAINABILITY
NSU is a LEED Gold campus.
- Chemicals: Must be Green Seal (GS-37) or EcoLogo certified. Use of bleach 
  is restricted to locker rooms and pandemic response protocols only.
- Equipment: Vacuums must be HEPA-rated (CRI Seal of Approval). Floor 
  machines must operate below 70 dBA.
- Consumables:
  -- Vendor Provides: Cleaning chemicals, pads, mops, machinery, PPE.
  -- University Provides: Toilet tissue, roll towels, hand soap, trash liners. 
     Vendor is responsible for inventory management.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.0 MANAGEMENT & STAFFING PLAN
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4.1 KEY PERSONNEL
The Vendor must provide a dedicated Account Director (must have 10+ years 
Higher Ed experience) and one Night Shift Manager. These roles are non-working 
supervisors (i.e., they do not push mops).

4.2 TRAINING REQUIREMENTS
Vendor must submit a training syllabus with the proposal covering:
1. OSHA Bloodborne Pathogens (annual).
2. GHS / Hazard Communication.
3. FERPA (Data Privacy) awareness.
4. Active Shooter / Emergency Lockout protocols.

4.3 LIVING WAGE & BENEFITS (MANDATORY)
Proposers must adhere to the University’s Living Wage Policy. The minimum 
hourly wage for entry-level custodians under this contract shall be no less 
than $18.50/hour. Proposals failing to meet this labor burden will be disqualified.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5.0 QUALITY ASSURANCE & KPI PENALTIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5.1 INSPECTIONS
- Joint Inspections: Once per month, the University Facilities Manager and 
  Vendor Account Director will inspect 10% of the square footage.
- Grading: Based on APPA audit forms.

5.2 DEDUCTIONS FOR NON-PERFORMANCE
The University reserves the right to deduct from the monthly invoice for 
performance failures:
- Missed Shift: $300 per employee per shift.
- Failure to secure building (Unlocked Doors): $500 per incident.
- Running out of supplies (Soap/Paper) during operating hours: $100 per incident.
- APPA Score below 80% for two consecutive months: 5% penalty on total invoice.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6.0 PROPOSAL CONTENTS (TABBED SECTIONS)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tab 1: Executive Summary
Tab 2: Corporate Experience (Provide 3 references of campuses >1M sq. ft.)
Tab 3: Operations Plan (Detailed staffing models, shift hours, equipment list)
Tab 4: Quality Control Plan (Technology used for tracking work orders)
Tab 5: Transition Plan (30-day mobilization timeline)
Tab 6: Financials (Audited financial statements for last 2 years)

*Note: Cost Proposal (Volume II) is submitted separately.*

